### =============================================================================
### FHIR Authorization Testing Examples (SMART v2)
### =============================================================================
### This file demonstrates RBAC authorization, SMART on FHIR v2 scopes,
### and capability statement enforcement.
###
### SMART v2 Scope Format: [context]/[resource].[cruds][?search-constraints]
### - context: patient, user, system, practitioner
### - resource: FHIR resource type or * for all
### - cruds: permissions in order (c=create, r=read, u=update, d=delete, s=search)
###
### Examples:
###   patient/Observation.rs (read + search)
###   user/Medication.cruds (all permissions)
###   system/Patient.cud (create, update, delete)
###   patient/Observation.rs?category=http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/observation-category|laboratory
###
### Requirements:
### 1. Start the FHIR server: dotnet run --project src/Application/Ignixa.Api
### 2. Use VS Code REST Client extension
### =============================================================================

@hostname = https://localhost:7058
@tenantId = 1

### =============================================================================
### SECTION 1: Token Generation (OpenIddict - Development)
### =============================================================================
### These examples show how to get test tokens for different scenarios.
### In development, OpenIddict provides a local OAuth server at /connect/token.
### SMART v2 scopes use CRUDS permissions (c=create, r=read, u=update, d=delete, s=search)

### 1.1 Get Admin Token (Full Access - CRUDS)
# @name adminToken
POST {{hostname}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=client_credentials
&client_id=fhir-admin-client
&client_secret=dev-secret
&scope=system/*.cruds

### 1.2 Get Clinician Token (User Scope - Read + Update + Search)
# @name clinicianToken
POST {{hostname}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password
&username=clinician@example.com
&password=Clinician123!
&scope=user/Patient.rs user/Observation.cruds user/Encounter.rs

### 1.3 Get Patient Token (Patient-Scoped SMART v2 - Read + Search only)
# @name patientToken
POST {{hostname}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password
&username=patient@example.com
&password=Patient123!
&scope=patient/Observation.rs patient/MedicationRequest.rs patient/Condition.rs
&patient_id=patient-123

### 1.4 Get ReadOnly Token (System Read + Search only)
# @name readOnlyToken
POST {{hostname}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=client_credentials
&client_id=readonly-client
&client_secret=readonly-secret
&scope=system/*.rs

### 1.5 Get Practitioner Token (Practitioner-Scoped SMART v2)
# @name practitionerToken
POST {{hostname}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password
&username=practitioner@example.com
&password=Practitioner123!
&scope=practitioner/Schedule.rs practitioner/Appointment.cruds
&fhirUser=Practitioner/practitioner-456

### 1.6 Get Token with Search Constraints (SMART v2 feature)
# @name constrainedToken
POST {{hostname}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password
&username=labtech@example.com
&password=LabTech123!
&scope=patient/Observation.rs?category=http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/observation-category|laboratory
&patient_id=patient-123

### =============================================================================
### SECTION 2: Unauthenticated Requests
### =============================================================================
### Only /metadata should be accessible without authentication

### 2.1 Get CapabilityStatement (Should Succeed - No Auth Required)
GET {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/metadata
Accept: application/fhir+json

### 2.2 Search Patients Without Auth (Should Fail - 401 Unauthorized)
GET {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/Patient
Accept: application/fhir+json

### 2.3 Get Patient Without Auth (Should Fail - 401 Unauthorized)
GET {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/Patient/example
Accept: application/fhir+json

### =============================================================================
### SECTION 3: RBAC Authorization (Role-Based)
### =============================================================================
### Tests role-based permissions configured in appsettings.json

### 3.1 Admin - Search Patients (Should Succeed)
GET {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/Patient?name=Smith
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken.response.body.access_token}}
Accept: application/fhir+json

### 3.2 Admin - Create Patient (Should Succeed)
POST {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/Patient
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/fhir+json

{
  "resourceType": "Patient",
  "name": [
    {
      "family": "TestAuth",
      "given": ["AdminCreated"]
    }
  ],
  "gender": "male"
}

### 3.3 Admin - Delete Patient (Should Succeed)
DELETE {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/Patient/test-delete-123
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken.response.body.access_token}}

### 3.4 ReadOnly - Search Patients (Should Succeed - Has Read Permission)
GET {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/Patient?name=Smith
Authorization: Bearer {{readOnlyToken.response.body.access_token}}
Accept: application/fhir+json

### 3.5 ReadOnly - Create Patient (Should Fail - 403 No Create Permission)
POST {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/Patient
Authorization: Bearer {{readOnlyToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/fhir+json

{
  "resourceType": "Patient",
  "name": [
    {
      "family": "TestAuth",
      "given": ["ShouldFail"]
    }
  ]
}

### 3.6 ReadOnly - Delete Patient (Should Fail - 403 No Delete Permission)
DELETE {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/Patient/test-delete-456
Authorization: Bearer {{readOnlyToken.response.body.access_token}}

### 3.7 Clinician - Create Observation (Should Succeed)
POST {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/Observation
Authorization: Bearer {{clinicianToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/fhir+json

{
  "resourceType": "Observation",
  "status": "final",
  "code": {
    "coding": [{
      "system": "http://loinc.org",
      "code": "8867-4",
      "display": "Heart rate"
    }]
  },
  "subject": { "reference": "Patient/patient-123" },
  "valueQuantity": {
    "value": 80,
    "unit": "beats/minute",
    "system": "http://unitsofmeasure.org",
    "code": "/min"
  }
}

### =============================================================================
### SECTION 4: SMART on FHIR Scopes (Patient Compartment Filtering)
### =============================================================================
### Tests SMART scope enforcement and patient compartment filtering

### 4.1 Patient Scope - Search Own Observations (Should Succeed - Filtered)
### Results should only include observations for patient-123
GET {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/Observation?code=8867-4
Authorization: Bearer {{patientToken.response.body.access_token}}
Accept: application/fhir+json

### 4.2 Patient Scope - Search All Observations (Should Be Filtered)
### Even without patient parameter, results filtered to patient-123
GET {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/Observation
Authorization: Bearer {{patientToken.response.body.access_token}}
Accept: application/fhir+json

### 4.3 Patient Scope - Search Another Patient's Data (Should Return Empty)
### Request another patient's observations - should get empty bundle
GET {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/Observation?patient=patient-456
Authorization: Bearer {{patientToken.response.body.access_token}}
Accept: application/fhir+json

### 4.4 Patient Scope - Read Own MedicationRequest (Should Succeed)
GET {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/MedicationRequest?patient=patient-123
Authorization: Bearer {{patientToken.response.body.access_token}}
Accept: application/fhir+json

### 4.5 Patient Scope - Write Observation (Should Fail - No Write Scope)
PUT {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/Observation/obs-123
Authorization: Bearer {{patientToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/fhir+json

{
  "resourceType": "Observation",
  "id": "obs-123",
  "status": "amended",
  "code": {
    "coding": [{
      "system": "http://loinc.org",
      "code": "8867-4",
      "display": "Heart rate"
    }]
  }
}

### 4.6 User Scope (Clinician) - Search All Patients (Should Succeed - No Filter)
GET {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/Patient
Authorization: Bearer {{clinicianToken.response.body.access_token}}
Accept: application/fhir+json

### =============================================================================
### SECTION 5: Capability Statement Enforcement
### =============================================================================
### Tests that server respects its CapabilityStatement
### Operations not in CapabilityStatement should return 403

### 5.1 Update AuditEvent (Should Fail - CapabilityStatement Doesn't Allow)
### AuditEvent typically only supports read/create, not update
PUT {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/AuditEvent/audit-123
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/fhir+json

{
  "resourceType": "AuditEvent",
  "id": "audit-123",
  "type": {
    "system": "http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/audit-event-type",
    "code": "rest",
    "display": "RESTful Operation"
  },
  "recorded": "2024-01-15T10:00:00Z",
  "agent": [{
    "who": { "display": "Test Agent" }
  }],
  "source": {
    "observer": { "display": "Test Source" }
  }
}

### 5.2 Delete AuditEvent (Should Fail - CapabilityStatement Doesn't Allow)
DELETE {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/AuditEvent/audit-456
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken.response.body.access_token}}

### 5.3 Read AuditEvent (Should Succeed - CapabilityStatement Allows)
GET {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/AuditEvent?date=ge2024-01-01
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken.response.body.access_token}}
Accept: application/fhir+json

### =============================================================================
### SECTION 6: Tenant Isolation
### =============================================================================
### Tests that users can only access their assigned tenant

### 6.1 Access Own Tenant (Should Succeed)
GET {{hostname}}/tenant/1/Patient
Authorization: Bearer {{clinicianToken.response.body.access_token}}
Accept: application/fhir+json

### 6.2 Access Different Tenant (Should Fail - 403 Tenant Isolation)
GET {{hostname}}/tenant/999/Patient
Authorization: Bearer {{clinicianToken.response.body.access_token}}
Accept: application/fhir+json

### =============================================================================
### SECTION 7: Bundle/Transaction Authorization
### =============================================================================
### Tests that bundle entries go through same authorization as direct calls

### 7.1 Transaction Bundle - Authorization Failure Atomicity (Should Fail - 403)
### ClinicianToken has user/Patient.rs (read+search ONLY), user/Observation.cruds (full permissions)
### The first entry (POST Patient) will fail authorization because clinician lacks create permission on Patient
### Transaction atomicity: When any entry fails authorization, the entire transaction is rolled back
### Expected: 403 Forbidden - demonstrates that bundle entries respect same authorization as direct requests
POST {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{clinicianToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/fhir+json

{
  "resourceType": "Bundle",
  "type": "transaction",
  "entry": [
    {
      "request": { "method": "POST", "url": "Patient" },
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Patient",
        "name": [{ "family": "BundleTest", "given": ["Transaction"] }]
      }
    },
    {
      "request": { "method": "POST", "url": "Observation" },
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Observation",
        "status": "final",
        "code": { "coding": [{ "system": "http://loinc.org", "code": "8867-4" }] },
        "subject": { "reference": "Patient/bundle-patient" }
      }
    }
  ]
}

### 7.2 Batch Bundle - Individual Entry Authorization
### Each entry authorized separately; failures don't affect other entries
POST {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{readOnlyToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/fhir+json

{
  "resourceType": "Bundle",
  "type": "batch",
  "entry": [
    {
      "request": { "method": "GET", "url": "Patient/example" }
    },
    {
      "request": { "method": "POST", "url": "Patient" },
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Patient",
        "name": [{ "family": "ShouldFail", "given": ["NoWritePermission"] }]
      }
    }
  ]
}

### =============================================================================
### SECTION 8: SMART Discovery Endpoints
### =============================================================================
### Tests SMART on FHIR discovery per HL7 specification

### 8.1 Get CapabilityStatement with Security Extension
### Should include rest.security with oauth-uris extension
GET {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/metadata
Accept: application/fhir+json

### 8.2 SMART Configuration Discovery
### Returns OAuth endpoints and supported capabilities
GET {{hostname}}/.well-known/smart-configuration
Accept: application/json

### =============================================================================
### SECTION 9: Error Response Validation
### =============================================================================
### Validates proper OperationOutcome responses for authorization failures

### 9.1 Expected 401 Unauthorized Response
GET {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/Patient
Accept: application/fhir+json
### Expected: 401 with OperationOutcome containing "Authentication required"

### 9.2 Expected 403 Forbidden Response (RBAC)
POST {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/Patient
Authorization: Bearer {{readOnlyToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/fhir+json

{
  "resourceType": "Patient",
  "name": [{ "family": "Test" }]
}
### Expected: 403 with OperationOutcome containing "No permission grants"

### 9.3 Expected 403 Forbidden Response (Capability)
PUT {{hostname}}/tenant/{{tenantId}}/AuditEvent/test
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/fhir+json

{
  "resourceType": "AuditEvent",
  "id": "test"
}
### Expected: 403 with OperationOutcome containing "Server does not support"

### =============================================================================
### SECTION 10: MCP Authorization (Model Context Protocol)
### =============================================================================
### Tests MCP tool access control requiring Mcp or Contributor roles.
### Jobs correspond to their operation type:
###   - import_job → requires create permission
###   - export_job → requires read permission
###   - list_jobs/get_job_status → requires read permission

### 10.1 Get MCP/Contributor Token (Full MCP Access)
# @name mcpToken
POST {{hostname}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=client_credentials
&client_id=mcp-client
&client_secret=mcp-secret
&scope=system/*.cruds

### 10.2 Get Contributor Token (Full MCP Access)
# @name contributorToken
POST {{hostname}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password
&username=contributor@example.com
&password=Contributor123!
&scope=system/*.cruds

### 10.3 Start Import Job (Requires create permission)
### Should succeed with Mcp or Contributor role
POST {{hostname}}/mcp
Authorization: Bearer {{mcpToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "start_import_job",
    "arguments": {
      "inputFiles": [
        {
          "type": "Patient",
          "url": "https://example.com/patients.ndjson"
        }
      ],
      "mode": "IncrementalLoad",
      "tenantId": 1
    }
  },
  "id": 1
}

### 10.4 Start Export Job (Requires read permission)
### Should succeed with Mcp or Contributor role
POST {{hostname}}/mcp
Authorization: Bearer {{mcpToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "start_export_job",
    "arguments": {
      "resourceTypes": ["Patient", "Observation"],
      "tenantId": 1
    }
  },
  "id": 2
}

### 10.5 List Jobs (Requires read permission)
POST {{hostname}}/mcp
Authorization: Bearer {{mcpToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "list_jobs",
    "arguments": {
      "tenantId": 1
    }
  },
  "id": 3
}

### 10.6 Get Job Status (Requires read permission)
POST {{hostname}}/mcp
Authorization: Bearer {{mcpToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "get_job_status",
    "arguments": {
      "jobId": "job-123",
      "jobType": "Import",
      "tenantId": 1
    }
  },
  "id": 4
}

### 10.7 MCP Access with ReadOnly Role (Should Fail - No MCP Access)
### ReadOnly role doesn't have McpAccess enabled
POST {{hostname}}/mcp
Authorization: Bearer {{readOnlyToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "start_import_job",
    "arguments": {
      "inputFiles": [
        {
          "type": "Patient",
          "url": "https://example.com/patients.ndjson"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  "id": 5
}
### Expected: 403 with "MCP access denied. Required role: Admin, SystemAdmin, Mcp, or Contributor."

### 10.8 MCP Access with Clinician Role (Should Fail - No MCP Access)
### Clinician role doesn't have McpAccess enabled
POST {{hostname}}/mcp
Authorization: Bearer {{clinicianToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "list_jobs",
    "arguments": {
      "tenantId": 1
    }
  },
  "id": 6
}
### Expected: 403 with "MCP access denied"

### 10.9 Search FHIR Resources via MCP (Requires read permission)
POST {{hostname}}/mcp
Authorization: Bearer {{mcpToken.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "search_fhir_resources",
    "arguments": {
      "resourceType": "Patient",
      "searchParams": {
        "name": "Smith"
      },
      "tenantId": 1
    }
  },
  "id": 7
}
